Fused heterocyclic compounds as orexin receptor modulators AbstractCertain disubstituted 3,8-diaza-bicyclo[4.2.0]octane and 3,6-diazabicyclo [3.2.0]heptane are described, which are useful as orexin inhibitors. Such compounds may be useful in pharmaceutical compositions and methods for the treatment of diseased states, disorders, and conditions mediated by orexin activity, such as insomnia. Claims




